# COMSATS Student Registry — DevOps Midterm

A full-stack Flask student registration portal with a production-grade dark UI.

## Stack
- **Backend**: Python Flask + SQLAlchemy (SQLite)
- **Frontend**: Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS (embedded)
- **Containerization**: Docker

---

## Run Locally

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
# Visit http://localhost:5000
```

---

## Docker Commands (Part 1 — 10 Marks)

```bash
# 1. Build the image
docker build -t student-portal .

# 2. Run locally in container
docker run -p 5000:5000 student-portal

# 3. Tag for Docker Hub (replace YOUR_USERNAME)
docker tag student-portal YOUR_USERNAME/student-portal:latest

# 4. Login to Docker Hub
docker login

# 5. Push to Docker Hub
docker push YOUR_USERNAME/student-portal:latest
```

---

## GitHub Commands (Part 3 — 5 Marks)

```bash
# Initialize repo
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/student-portal.git

# Stage all files
git add .

# Commit
git commit -m "feat: add student portal with Docker support"

# Push
git push -u origin main

# Pull (if needed)
git pull origin main
```

---

## Features
- Register students with name, roll, department, semester
- Delete students
- Search and sort table
- Duplicate roll number validation
- Live clock
- Animated dark UI with grid background